86972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fujairah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fujairah\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The former UAAP standout edged Kazakhstan's Sofiya Aktayeva, 15-14, in the final to become the first fencer from the Philippines to qualify for the Olympics in over three decades since Walter Torres competed in the 1992 Barcelona Games.\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 574, \"end\": 584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9614334274779504, \"rank\": 0.038933350645970526, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 587, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sofia\", \"score\": 0.999998056232541, \"rank\": 1.943771266750294e-06, \"text\": \"Sofiya\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sofia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sofia\"}, {\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.5487420611488243, \"rank\": 0.42102463173641463, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tested in every way possible in the finale, Catantan powered through and delivered an impassioned performance.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catantan trailed 9-12 in the third and final round after she incurred a one-point penalty following a red card from the referee.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 1021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the 22-year-old Catantan bounced back and scored four of the next five points to tie the count at 13-13.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The last point of that stretch, however, came at a cost as Catantan hurt her left knee off a lunge.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the same knee Catantaninjuredlast year before her gold-medal match in the Southeast Asian Games in Phnom Penh, Cambodia.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asian_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999999743068, \"rank\": 2.5633585719156904e-11, \"text\": \"Southeast Asian Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asian_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Southeast_Asian_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 1340, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phnom_Penh\", \"score\": 0.9999996982522135, \"rank\": 3.0173332511932527e-07, \"text\": \"Phnom Penh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phnom_Penh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phnom_Penh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then worried of aggravating the injury, Catantan surrendered and settled for silver.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catantan, though, refused to be denied this time as she opted to continue with the match against Aktayeva after a five-minute injury timeout.\", \"from\": 1449, \"to\": 1590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the two traded points for a 14-14 tie, Catantan pulled through and scored the final point that allowed her to book her ticket to Paris.\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999998668811347, \"rank\": 1.3311886792748113e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Overcome with emotions, Catantan fell on her knees and cried with her hands covering her face.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1829, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catantan beat out 13 other fencers who were vying for the lone Olympic spot up for grabs in women's foil.\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1936, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She finished the pool round as the No.\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"4 seed and got a bye in the round of 16 before she disposed of Oman's Israa Al Siyabi in the quarterfinals and South Korea's Hong Sena in the semifinals.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oman_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999873136350567, \"rank\": 1.267461620906589e-05, \"text\": \"Oman\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oman_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oman_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6892285800290019, \"rank\": 0.45080916628972767, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea_national_under-23_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2184, \"entities\": []}]}"